	(iii) If $|x|=2^l3^s$, where $0<l\leq n$, $0<s\leq m$, then $\left\langle x\right\rangle $ contains an element of order 6, let it be $y$. Let $X_1$ and $X_2$ be subsets of $\left\langle y \right\rangle$, where $X_1$ contains two elements of order 6, and two elements of order 3; and $X_2$ contains one element of order 2, and two elements of order 6.	
