	\noindent\textbf{Subcase 2b(iii)}: If $p\geq 5$, then the elements in $G$ of order $q$ and $pq$ are not a power of the elements of order $p^2$, and vise versa. Note that $G$ contains at least one element of orders q, at least four elements of order $pq$, and at least twenty elements of order $p^2$. It follows that $\overline{\mathscr{P}^*(G)}$ contains $K_{3,7}$ as a subgraph, so $\gamma ({\overline{\mathscr{P}^*(G)}})>1$ and $\overline{\gamma} {(\overline{\mathscr{P}^*(G)})}>1$. \\
